The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval (PIR) with colluding servers and eavesdroppers, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely categories. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures for PIR, which could fall under cs.DS and cs.DB. Finally, the paper involves communication complexity, which could fall under cs.CC.
